programme.desc: El Dr. Stefan Stefanov, un cirujano respetado y querido, se ve envuelto en un escándalo tras la sospechosa muerte de un paciente. Una periodista emprende una investigacion para averiguar que ocurrio en realidad.

programme.title: La suegra
programme.desc: La vida pacífica de una pareja desata en el caos mientras los límites de la privacidad son demolidos por la madre de uno de ellos.

programme.title: Mafia en la sangre
programme.desc: Un ambicioso magistrado se traslada al sur de Italia para acabar con la mafia calabresa. En lugar de atacar a los hombres violentos y crueles de la organizacion, espera apelar a sus esposas e hijos para traer la paz a la region.

programme.title: LandKrimi
programme.desc: Una oficial es llevada al límite cuando un asesinato la obliga a cuestionar a sus allegados.

programme.title: Enterrado
programme.desc: Un capataz tiene una aventura con la mujer de su mejor amigo, tambien minero. Para encontrarse con su amante, envía a su amigo a las lejanas y peligrosas minas de carbon.

programme.title: Expiacion
programme.desc: La investigacion de una reliquia catolica robada da un giro inesperado cuando un detective desentraña una red que sugiere que el crimen tiene implicaciones políticas de gran alcance.

programme.title: Matrimonio mortal
programme.desc: El cuerpo de Maud yace al pie de la montaña Sainte-Victoire. Interrogado por la policía, su marido, Jean, explica que ella se cayo. El caso se cierra sin más investigacion. Una semana despues, un testimonio siembra la duda sobre el accidente.

programme.desc: A mid-level drug dealer (Daniel Craig) must perform two final tasks for his boss (Kenneth Cranham) before he can quit the business for good.

programme.desc: Fired from his corporate job, a man (Anthony Mackie) agrees to impregnate his ex-fiancee (Kerry Washington) and a slew of lesbians for money.

programme.title: Super/Man: The Christopher Reeve Story
programme.desc: Actor Christopher Reeve rises to stardom when he lands the role of Superman in the 1970s. When a horse-riding accident leaves him paralyzed in 1995, Reeve spends the rest of his life searching for a cure for spinal cord injuries.

programme.title: Nebraska
programme.desc: A man (Will Forte) accompanies his aging, cantankerous father (Bruce Dern) on a long road trip from Billings, Mont., to Lincoln, Neb., to claim a cash prize that might not actually exist.

programme.desc: The true story about the keepers (Jessica Chastain, Johan Heldenbergh) of the Warsaw Zoo who helped save hundreds of people from Nazi hands during World War II.

programme.title: Echoes
programme.desc: An author and his family must survive a hellish night.

programme.title: The King Tide
programme.desc: After a child with mysterious powers washes ashore their idyllic island village, the once peaceful community devolves into civil war, torn over the belief that the child is the next savior.

programme.title: Out of Darkness

programme.title: Room
programme.desc: Held captive for years in an enclosed space, a woman (Brie Larson) and her young son (Jacob Tremblay) finally gain their freedom, allowing the boy to experience the outside world for the first time.

programme.title: Little Children
programme.desc: A dissatisfied housewife (Kate Winslet) and the husband (Patrick Wilson) of a documentary filmmaker (Jennifer Connelly) have secret trysts while their spouses are at work.

programme.title: We Grown Now
programme.desc: In 1992 best friends Malik and Eric traverse the city of Chicago, looking to escape the mundaneness of school and the hardships of growing up in public housing. They soon find their unbreakable bond challenged when a tragedy shakes their community.

programme.title: The Peasants
programme.desc: Jagna finds herself caught between the desires of a rich farmer, his eldest son and other men.

programme.title: The Wolf Man
programme.desc: Bitten by a werewolf, an aristocrat (Lon Chaney) grows fangs, fur and a muzzle, then begs his father (Claude Rains) for help.

programme.title: The Craft
programme.desc: Teen misfits befriend a suicidal newcomer and strike back at their tormentors with witchcraft in Los Angeles.

programme.title: The Summit
programme.desc: During a presidential summit in Chile, Argentinas president Hernán Blanco goes through family drama affecting the relationship with his daughter while facing the most important moment in his career.

programme.title: Family Plot
programme.desc: Two frauds (Bruce Dern, Barbara Harris) seeking a womans heir cross paths with another couple planning a kidnapping scheme for diamonds.

programme.title: Asteroid City
programme.desc: World-changing events spectacularly disrupt the itinerary of a Junior Stargazer/Space Cadet convention in an American desert town circa 1955.

programme.title: You Hurt My Feelings
programme.desc: A novelists long-standing marriage is suddenly upended when she overhears her husband give his honest reaction to her latest book.

programme.title: A Thousand and One
programme.desc: Unapologetic and free-spirited Inez kidnaps her 6-year-old son, Terry, from the foster care system. They set out to reclaim their sense of home, identity and stability in a rapidly changing New York City.

programme.title: Freuds Last Session
programme.desc: On the eve of World War II, Sigmund Freud and C.S. Lewis gather to discuss the existence of God and the future of mankind.
